quence="00" designation="us-only"><addressbook><last-name>Steininger</last-name><first-name>Jeff</first-name><address><city>St. Mary's</city><state>OH</state><country>US</country></address></addressbook></inventor></inventors></us-parties></us-bibliographic-data-application><abstract id="abstract"><p id="p-0001" num="0000">A liquid metering assembly is described and which includes a container for enclosing a source of a liquid to be dispensed; a container cap defining a dispensing aperture and a vent aperture which is releasably affixed to the container; a moveable diaphragm releasably cooperating with the container cap, and coupled in fluid flowing relation relative to the dispensing aperture, and wherein the moveable diaphragm has a valve member; and a moveable liquid volume control member which cooperates with the moveable diaphragm, and wherein, when a predetermined suction is applied to the dispensing aperture of the container cap, a user may withdraw a given volume of liquid from the beverage container.</p></abstract></us-patent-application>